records.addlTxt:
Defendant Tyler W Horbinski in court with attorney Paul E Bucher.  Lesli S. Boese appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Sentencing argument by Atty. Boese and Atty. Bucher.  Statement by defendant's father, grandfather and cousin.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

 3 Years 6 months Imprisonment (Credit - 0 days )
- 1 Year 6 months  of Initial Confinement
- 2 Years of Extended Supervision

Term of Probation:   3 Years

Conditions of Probation:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Mental Health Evaluation and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment/schooling;
- Submit a written apology to the victim;
- No contact with victim or family members other than the letter of apology.
- Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge

Restitution: $415.50 to the Village of Eagle  (already paid)

Costs: $268.00 
DNA Surcharge:  $250.00	
(To be paid as a condition of probation during the first 12 months.)

Condition Time: 90 days Huber NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS -  Can be served in Winnebago County only if served in the Institution.  To commence forthwith.  

Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is not eligible for the Substance Abuse Program

Expunction is conditionally granted in 5 years upon completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.  Defendant must Petition the Court in writing upon successful completion of the sentence.
